## 4. Local Environment Setup

### Step 1 — Clone the Repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-team/trekku-workspace.git
cd trekku-workspace
```

### Step 2 — Backend Setup
```bash
cd backend
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate           # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**`requirements.txt` contents:**
```
fastapi
uvicorn
firebase-admin
requests
python-dotenv
pydantic
groq
huggingface_hub
pytest
httpx
```

### Step 3 — Create `backend/.env`
Copy from `.env.example` and fill in your values:
```
# SerpAPI Keys (one per team member account)
SERPAPI_KEY_1=your_key_here
SERPAPI_KEY_2=your_key_here
SERPAPI_KEY_3=your_key_here
SERPAPI_KEY_4=your_key_here
SERPAPI_KEY_5=your_key_here

# Firebase
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=trekku-kms
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@trekku-kms.iam.gserviceaccount.com

# Groq
GROQ_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Hugging Face
HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=your_key_here

# App
ENVIRONMENT=development
```

### Step 4 — Create `backend/.env.example` (commit this, not `.env`)
```
SERPAPI_KEY_1=
SERPAPI_KEY_2=
SERPAPI_KEY_3=
SERPAPI_KEY_4=
SERPAPI_KEY_5=
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=
GROQ_API_KEY=
HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=
ENVIRONMENT=development
```

### Step 5 — Run Backend Locally
```bash
cd backend
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```
API will be available at: `http://localhost:8000`
Auto-generated docs at: `http://localhost:8000/docs`

### Step 6 — Frontend Setup
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
```

Create `frontend/.env.local`:
```
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

Run frontend:
```bash
npm start
```

