## 6. Claude Code Prompt to Generate `knowledge_capture.py`

Once all steps above are complete, use this prompt in Claude Code:

```
Read the PRD at docs/prd.md and the existing files:
- backend/config.py (Firebase init)
- backend/models.py (Pydantic schemas)
- backend/database.py (get_record, set_record stubs)

Generate backend/knowledge_capture.py with these functions:
1. seed_database() — one-time batch fetch for TREKKU_SEED list
2. ttl_checker(entity_id, collection) — returns FRESH / STALE / NOT_FOUND
3. trend_tracker(topic_name) — increments counter, flags re-fetch at threshold 10
4. quota_tracker() — rotates across SERPAPI_KEY_1 to _5, returns FALLBACK when all exhausted
5. fetch_and_parse(query, entity_type) — calls SerpAPI, maps to clean schema
6. store_to_firebase(record, collection) — writes to Firestore with TTL fields

TTL rules: hotels metadata 30 days, hotels pricing 7 days,
attractions 60 days, flights 7 days.

Also generate backend/tests/test_knowledge_capture.py
covering all functions as described in the PRD.
```

